column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
pH = 5.53- no filamentous algae- some grass clumps floating- 2 eagles- caught 2 perch (6") - 2 sunfish (3") - 2 bluegills (5") - 6 bass (7") .
pH 5.73- mostly cloudy- wind 5 mph- 65 F- saw a loon- bullfrogs calling- no young water fowl seen yet- no filamentous algae.

6/27: first indication of filamentous algae on N end of lake. depth about 3 feet. very thick by lehmer home.- pH 5.69- water depth is down to 13 feet- no filamentous algae on deep end yet- partly cloudy- calm- 80 F.
Mostly sunny- 68 F- wind 5-10 mph- no filamentous algae on south side of lake- pH 5.75.
pH 5.6- clear and sunny with glass-like surface- 0 mph winds- filamentous algae covering the entire shoreline out to 100-200'- algae not in deepest part at 12-14'
Cloudy- 62 degrees- pair of loons- mallards- osprey- the lake is down 2 feet- no filamentous algae on south end of lake yet.  Many small 1-2" bluegill schools.

Clear- slight ripple. lake used heavily over July 4. saw 2 osprey- 2 loons. no algae on south end of lake- sparse on north end. no algae around the barley straw. more homeowners leaving aquatic species like lily pads and pickerel weeds in.

Lake is more murky than last year. little boat traffic all week.  Mostly cloudy. cool all week- around 65 degrees.  Still no algae on south end of lake or around barley straw.  Slight increase in algae on north end. 1 osprey- 1 heron and kingfisher.

Lake level up 1 foot from last reading. Very calm- partly cloudy- 75 degrees. 40 mallards. No algae at deep hole- some found in SW corner toward bottom- thick mass in west corner 1 foot from top and none along the NE shoreline- slight amount on east side.
2 eagles on lake.  All other water fowl gone.  Moderate amount of algae on bottom .  Replaced 6 barley straw set ups.
Sunny- calm- partly cloudy- temperature is 90 degrees F- heavy boat traffic and swim activity- and the filamentous algae is heavy.
Mostly cloudy- slight wind- 70 degrees- and filamentous algae heavy in all areas of the lake except at 11' depth.
Algae has started to die and sink as water temperatures drop.  Sea gulls- loons- osprey- one eagle- and mallard with five babies.
Eagle- no algae- and 500 large mouth bass stocked on 10/10/01 (6-8" fish)

Very little fliamentous algae. A few small patches- many turtles- frogs- bluegill and bass.  Ducks with ducklings (mallards). A pair of loons- eagles- and mergansers in spring.  Frogs = green- bullfrog and Copes tree frog.
Heavy algae at NW and NE edge. Scattered large clumps at east and SE edge. Pair of loons still around. Many small bluegill.
Heavy filamentous algae all over the lake.  Loons have left.
filamentous algae- full bloom. Mats of grass floating. Cloudy-calm
Lake Level 3 feet down- secci only 1/2 foot from bottom- very clear. Algae not as bad this year. Plants moving from algae to more vascular. Thick mats of water milfoil coming up from bottom.
Lake level very low! More Vascular plants. No exotics. Filamentous algae 25%- 2 loons
Lake level up one foot- but still low. No exotics- filamentous algae at its worst- 75% of lake. Loons gone.
Filamentous algae starting early. Pair of loons back- no babies. Eagles. Large mouth bass fishing is great.

Lots of rain but water level is still low. Loons- osprey- eagle. "grass" covering the bottom of lake. Filamentous algae minimal compared to previous years. No filmentous algae by SW bay and north side.
A lot of precipitation this year. No filamentous algae. Water quality is poor this year. More boat traffic.
Clarity improving - algae sank to bottom. Still not as clear.
water depth is 12 feet. no filamentous algae. 2 loons.
windy and beautiful. Minimal filamentous algae. More watershield patches on SE corner by the boat landing.
Depth of lake 12.5 feet. Clearest the lake has ever been. Minimal filamentous algae. Large amount of watershield. Huge masses of bladderwort.
Rain 2 of last three days. Heavy pollen on lake. Sunny and calm.
watershield advanced on east shore. Some algae. Many northerns.
Sunny and calm. Rained the day before.
watershield and bladderwort increase. Water is clear. First loon with baby.
Some boat traffic early. Clear and calm. Rained last night.
light breeze out of the north. partly cloudy.
Weather is clear and 70 degrees F
Loon with baby this year.  Large amounts of Water shield.  Removing some with cutter.  Large masses of Bladder Wart floating.  No reports of EWM around the entire perimeter of the lake.

Less frogs this year.  No baby loons.  COVID increase boat traffic.  Increased amount of Watershield.  Onterra doing density studies. Less frogs this year.  No baby loons.  COVID increase boat traffic.  Increased amount of Watershield.  Onterra doing density studies.
